Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Meanwhile, peel the @potatoes{450%g} and chop into 2cm chunks. Trim and peel the @parsnip{1} and chop into 2cm chunks. Add the potatoes and parsnips to the pan of boiling water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and fry until starting to brown, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. While the chicken fries, trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways.

Stir the leek and @dried thyme{1/2%tsp} into the chicken and cook until the leek has softened, another ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @KNORR chicken stock powder{1/2%cube}, bring to the boil then reduce the heat and simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}. Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Mash the cooked potatoes and parsnips together with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. > TIP: Add a knob of butter or a splash of milk to the mash if you have some!

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Stir the sweetcorn into the chicken mixture. Season to taste with @salt{} and @black pepper{} then transfer into an #ovenproof dish{}. Spoon the mash on top and spread out so it covers the filling evenly.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} evenly over then grill until golden and bubbly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Serve the pie and enjoy!